text: Cecil County is a county in the U.S. state of Maryland. As of the 2020 census, the population was 103,725. The county seat is Elkton. Cecil is named after Cecil Calvert, the first Proprietary Governor of the Province (colony) of Maryland. == References == Category:Maryland counties Category:1674 establishments Category:1670s establishments in the Thirteen Colonies Category:17th-century establishments in Maryland
